FactoryCb`\n   - Registers filter dependencies via `DependencyManager`\n   - Stores the filter factory in `filter_factories_` list\n\n2. **FilterFactoryCb** (envoy/http/filter_factory.h, line 24): A std::function type that represents a lazily-created filter factory: `std::function<void(FilterChainFactoryCallbacks& callbacks)>`\n\nThe helper class uses `FilterConfigProviderManager` to manage static and dynamic filter configurations, supporting both inline configurations and ECDS.\n\n### Runtime Filter Chain Creation\n\n**Flow**: \n1. HTTP connection arrives → `ConnectionManagerImpl::newStream()` (conn_manager_impl.cc, lines 378-427)\n2. Creates `ActiveStream` which initializes a `DownstreamFilterManager` (line 782-789)\n3. Request headers arrive → `ActiveStream::decodeHeaders()` (conn_manager_impl.cc, line 1132)\n4. Filter chain creation triggered at line 1348: `const bool upgrade_rejected = filter_manager_.createFilterChain() == false;`\n\n**FilterManager::createFilterChain()** (source/common/http/filter_manager.cc, lines 1550-1586):\n- Checks if this is an upgrade request (WebSocket, CONNECT, etc.)\n- If upgrade detected, calls `FilterChainFactory::createUpgradeFilterChain()` with the appropriate upgrade type\n- Otherwise, calls `FilterChainFactory::createFilterChain()` with the default filter chain\n- Both methods instantiate the filter chain via `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()`\n\n### Filter Chain Construction\n\n**FilterChainFactory Interface** (envoy/http/filter_factory.h, lines 89-119):\n- `createFilterChain(FilterChainManager& manager, bool only_create_if_configured, const FilterChainOptions& options)`: Creates the default HTTP filter chain\n- `createUpgradeFilterChain(absl::string_view upgrade, const UpgradeMap* per_route_upgrade_map, FilterChainManager& manager)`: Creates upgrade-specific filter chain\n\n**HttpConnectionManagerConfig Implementation** (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h, lines 127-250+):\nExtends `Http::FilterChainFactory` and implements both methods (config.cc, lines 780-817):\n- Calls `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` with the pre-built `filter_factories_` list\n- For upgrades, selects between default or upgrade-specific filter factories based on upgrade type and route configuration\n\n**FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()** (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc, lines 17-47):\n- Iterates through the list of `FilterFactoryProvider` objects\n- For each non-disabled filter, retrieves its factory callback via `provider->config()`\n- Calls `manager.applyFilterFactoryCb()` with the factory callback and filter context\n- Injects a `MissingConfigFilter` if a dynamic config provider fails to load\n\n### Filter Chain Manager Integration\n\n**FilterChainManager Interface** (envoy/http/filter_factory.h, lines 70-81):\n- Implemented by `DownstreamFilterManager` (which extends `FilterManager`)\n- Method: `applyFilterFactoryCb(FilterContext context, FilterFactoryCb& factory)`\n- This method is the bridge between factory callbacks and actual filter instantiation\n\n**FilterManager::applyFilterFactoryCb()** (source/common/http/filter_manager.cc, line 551):\n- Creates a `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl` wrapping the FilterManager\n- Invokes the factory callback with this callbacks object\n- The factory callback calls methods on `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` to register filters\n\n**FilterChainFactoryCallbacks Interface** (envoy/http/filter.h, lines 1224-1257):\n- `addStreamDecoderFilter(Http::StreamDecoderFilterSharedPtr filter)`: Adds decoder-only filter\n- `addStreamEncoderFilter(Http::StreamEncoderFilterSharedPtr filter)`: Adds encoder-only filter\n- `addStreamFilter(Http::StreamFilterSharedPtr filter)`: Adds bidirectional decoder/encoder filter\n- `addAccessLogHandler(AccessLog::InstanceSharedPtr handler)`: Adds access log handler\n\n**FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl** (source/common/http/filter_manager.h, lines 913-949):\nThe FilterManager's private implementation of FilterChainFactoryCallbacks:\n- `addStreamDecoderFilter()`: Creates `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter` wrapper and appends to `decoder_filters_`\n- `addStreamEncoderFilter()`: Creates `ActiveStreamEncoderFilter` wrapper and prepends to `encoder_filters_`\n- `addStreamFilter()`: Creates both decoder and encoder wrappers for dual filters\n\n### Filter Execution Order\n\nDuring request processing:\n1. **Decoding**: `FilterManager::decodeHeaders()` iterates through decoder_filters from front to back\n2. **Encoding**: `FilterManager::encodeHeaders()` iterates through encoder_filters from back to front\n\nThis ensures decoder filters execute in configured order, while encoder filters execute in reverse order (typical for request/response asymmetry).\n\n### Key Design Points\n\n1. **Configuration-driven**: Filter chains are defined entirely in protobuf, supporting both static and dynamic (ECDS) configurations\n2. **Lazy instantiation**: FilterFactoryCb callbacks delay actual filter creation until the stream reaches the filter chain creation point\n3. **Dual manager pattern**: Separate FilterChainFactory (registration) and FilterChainManager (execution) interfaces provide clean separation of concerns\n4. **Bidirectional filtering**: Filters can implement decoder-only, encoder-only, or bidirectional interfaces, with execution order automatically handled\n5. **Upgrade handling**: Special protocol upgrades (WebSocket, CONNECT) get their own filter chain if configured, falling back to default chain if not\n6. **Route-based overrides**: Per-route filter configuration allows routes to enable filters disabled by default or override upgrade behavior"
